peopleAlsoAskedFor.question: Do architects need to be registered in Australia?
peopleAlsoAskedFor.title: How to become an architect in Australia - UNSW Sydney
peopleAlsoAskedFor.answers: What qualifications do you need to be an architect? Upon graduating from the Bachelor and Master of Architecture, you need to pass the Architectural Practice Examination and then register with the Architect Registration Board. Once this is done, you are recognised as a registered architect in Australia.
